n a neighborhood which has been recently annexed by a city. I am now included in that city's coverage area for fire department services. However, there are still some issues between the city and the state regarding the funding of the department. (Much of the department's funding is via local property taxes, but there is supplementation from the state.) Should I refrain from calling the fire department when I need their services, if I am aware that the funding issues are not yet resolved? Or should I call them to come and put out a fire in my home when I need it? &#10;Obviously, I should use the service that is provided. The solution is not for me to forego the service; the solution is for those who are involved with the funding process to fix the issues that are occurring. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1075" language="en" documentId="647" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="KRAMV" date="Last edited 09/06/2013" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://community.babycenter.com/post/a44369503/home_schooling_debate_this_hypothetical?cpg=36" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="647" notes="" title="Home schooling: Debate this hypothetical"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="87"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="88" end="166"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="167" end="213"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="214" end="864"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="55" sofa="1" begin="865" end="1075"/><types:PersuasivenessAnnotationMetaData xmi:id="59" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" annotator="annotator1" isPersuasive="true" labelDetailed="P1" isGold="false" annotationBatchName="batch1-first100docs" conflictResolvingAnnotation="false"/><types:PersuasivenessAnnotationMetaData xmi:id="71" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" annotator="annotator2" isPersuasive="true" labelDetailed="P1" isGold="false" annotationBatchName="batch1-first100docs" c